atholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":29,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705188,"age":38,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705189,"age":73,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Gilbert De Glanville was born about 1186, in Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 son with Gilbert Glanville."},"et":{"ABT 1186–":"umbes 1186–Surnud","1200–1266":"1200–1266","1235–1280":"1235–1280","1186–Female":"1186–Surnud","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","ABT 1186":"umbes 1186","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1266":"1266","1200":"1200","1186":"1186","Abt 1235":"umbes 1235","1280":"1280","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Bowsley, Antley, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1186–":"noin 1186–Kuollut","120